{"type":"text","timestamp":1777794619494,"sessionID":"ses_21332ae13ffezuk9lTv3NrWP2f","part":{"id":"prt_decd108630015pHFabzpfSE4At","messageID":"msg_decd0ff93001Iz2o3PZ0IYsStZ","sessionID":"ses_21332ae13ffezuk9lTv3NrWP2f","type":"text","text":"Wrote `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r10s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary of proposal:**\n\n- **Category:** micro_opt (pattern: \"constrain upstream, let downstream DCE\")\n- **Change scope:** 2 files, zero pipeline-register struct edits (avoids the well-documented formal tarpit from r4s0/r5s1/r5s2/r6s0/r6s1/r7s0/r7s2/r8s0)\n- **Mechanism:** AND `reg_write` with `instr[11:7] != 5'b0` in id_stage, making the forward_unit's `rd != 5'b0` gates redundant. The priority-encoder cone feeding EX-stage operand muxes loses one LUT4 level.\n- **Confidence:** low (Yosys may have already CSE'd this constraint, in which case it's a no-op — per lessons r4s1/r8s1/r9s0/r9s2, CSE is aggressive on GW2AR). The hypothesis is defensively framed: if already optimized, no regression; if not, marginal Fmax gain on a hot cone.\n- **Risk mitigation:** No struct field renames, no redirect-cone restructuring, no id_ex_t edits, no pre-flop MEM mux (all confirmed failure modes). The change is semantically identical to what RVFI `rd_wen` already computes at retirement — propagating that constraint one stage earlier.","time":{"start":1777794615395,"end":1777794619491}}}
