{"type":"text","timestamp":1777796543645,"sessionID":"ses_2131677e7ffecydQ1T4r3asgUc","part":{"id":"prt_decee61010012OmjrWxDW8Oq7N","messageID":"msg_decee584f001gO3k0YPFxbMTtL","sessionID":"ses_2131677e7ffecydQ1T4r3asgUc","type":"text","text":"Wrote hypothesis `hyp-20260503-001-r11s0` — **Remove dead `ex_mem_t.branch_taken` / `branch_target` fields (33 unused FFs)**.\n\n**Finding**: grep confirms these two fields are written into the EX/MEM register by `ex_stage` but read by **zero** consumers — not `mem_stage`, not `wb_stage`, not the RVFI top-level logic. They're pure dead flops; `ex_mem_t.pc_next` already carries the resolved next-PC.\n\n**Why this fits the winning patterns, not the tarpits**:\n- Matches r1s0's \"reduce silicon contributing nothing to the retirement datapath\" winning pattern\n- Avoids every documented tarpit: no `id_ex_t` rename (r7s0), no fetch-redirect cone rewrite (r8s0/r9s2), no regfile-reset change (r4s0/r5s0/r6s1), no load-data cone reshape (r6s0), no ALU operand widening (r7s1), no `ctrl.reg_write` domain change (r10s0), no threaded new fields (r10s1)\n- `ex_mem_t` edits per se are formally safe — r10s1 appended fields and passed formal (regressed only on FPGA)\n- Removes 33 FFs (~1.8% of 1861) from a near-full 94.8% fabric; primary hope is better Gowin FF-slice packing\n\n**Confidence: low** — Yosys *should* already DCE these. Fitness delta conservatively estimated at +2%. Clean scope (3 files, all mechanical).","time":{"start":1777796538625,"end":1777796543643}}}
