{"type":"text","timestamp":1777801442903,"sessionID":"ses_212cbcc4fffebpiL6Hrcu0tTBS","part":{"id":"prt_ded39196e0017ZM8f6srehH3wG","messageID":"msg_ded343477001MR2oUb1dC0raFo","sessionID":"ses_212cbcc4fffebpiL6Hrcu0tTBS","type":"text","text":"Looking at this situation carefully:\n\n- Current best is r4s2 (+17.73%, JAL fast-path) — a zero-storage local win\n- Predictor space is exhausted (6+ regressions confirmed the r4s2 pattern doesn't generalize)\n- Many \"obvious\" micro-opts have regressed due to Yosys CSE having already optimized them\n- Formal tarpit list is large: id_ex_t edits, reset semantics, shadow state, PC-redirect cone reshaping, RVFI observability changes\n- r13s0/r13s1/r13s2 just narrowed the safe space further\n\nLet me check for any relevant prior J-imm sharing attempts.","time":{"start":1777801435502,"end":1777801442902}}}
