{"type":"text","timestamp":1777782508271,"sessionID":"ses_213e85e67ffe0SVaGLp8k2t34z","part":{"id":"prt_dec183f35001Ztd063KejD2Zui","messageID":"msg_dec183a6c0018PMd9EOkx77goR","sessionID":"ses_213e85e67ffe0SVaGLp8k2t34z","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r1s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: Collapse the three always-computed 32×32 multipliers in `alu.sv` (`mul_ss`, `mul_uu`, `mul_su`) into a single shared 33×33 signed multiplier with alu_op-selected operand sign-extensions. MUL reads `prod[31:0]`; MULH/MULHU/MULHSU read `prod[63:32]`. Division and the `RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS` branch are untouched — ALTOPS keeps formal BMC tractable; arithmetic correctness is still gated by `test_alu.py` + cosim against the Python ISS.\n\n**Why micro_opt**: This is a pure data-path microarchitectural tightening — no pipeline depth or topology change, no ISA change, no predictor. Targets the EX critical path on a core whose current Fmax (135 MHz) contributes linearly to fitness, plus saves DSP/LUT pressure on the Tang Nano 20K.","time":{"start":1777782505269,"end":1777782508266}}}
