{"type":"text","timestamp":1777783516650,"sessionID":"ses_213d960fdffe1TJ09PlVYrpLXA","part":{"id":"prt_dec27a6110011qQEdcPjnx5uVS","messageID":"msg_dec279ff20012iGfylQizl0vDi","sessionID":"ses_213d960fdffe1TJ09PlVYrpLXA","type":"text","text":"Wrote the hypothesis to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r2s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: Micro-opt proposal — consolidate ADD/SUB/SLT/SLTU and the ex-stage branch comparator onto a single shared 33-bit subtractor in `alu.sv`, exposing `eq`/`lt_signed`/`lt_unsigned` flags. This mirrors the r1s0 multiplier-sharing win (+9.47%) by collapsing redundant arithmetic silicon hanging off the forward-mux outputs, shrinking the EX-cone carry chain and rs1/rs2 fanout on GW2AR. Arithmetic semantics unchanged, so ALTOPS/formal/cosim should all still pass. Expected ~4% Fmax-driven CoreMark gain, medium confidence.","time":{"start":1777783514641,"end":1777783516648}}}
