{"type":"text","timestamp":1777785061344,"sessionID":"ses_213c30d33ffeW0EWfCe6z9RYpn","part":{"id":"prt_dec3f2e10001jh2lCFPOHumPGP","messageID":"msg_dec3f24c6001lQKshy4A6Is206","sessionID":"ses_213c30d33ffeW0EWfCe6z9RYpn","type":"text","text":"Wrote `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r3s0.yaml`.\n\n**Hypothesis:** Convert `reg_file.sv` into the canonical Yosys-inferred distributed-RAM pattern so GW2AR maps it to LUT4-SSRAM instead of 1024 flops + two 32:1 read-mux trees.\n\n**Why this slot (micro_opt):**\n- Direct response to the r2s2 lesson — \"reclaim area elsewhere first.\" The regfile holds >55% of the FF budget and dominates the ID read-mux area while being nowhere near the critical path.\n- Bit-identical behavior (async read, write-first bypass, x0 hardwire) — no IPC delta; entire fitness move flows through Fmax × routing headroom.\n- Avoids every previously-punished class: doesn't touch the PC/fetch cone (r1s2), doesn't add comparators to the ALU (r2s0), doesn't insert muxes on the imem→decoder path (r2s1), doesn't add predictor storage (r2s2).\n- Single-file change with a clean fallback: if Gowin doesn't infer SSRAM, area is unchanged — no correctness risk.","time":{"start":1777785056784,"end":1777785061343}}}
