{"type":"text","timestamp":1777787455573,"sessionID":"ses_213a0fee5ffe3eqfnPNjHgkXqT","part":{"id":"prt_dec63b62a001oWJnVCcMbcs01b","messageID":"msg_dec63b0f9001e8KqTWBc0naqHw","sessionID":"ses_213a0fee5ffe3eqfnPNjHgkXqT","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r5s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:**\n\nCategory: `micro_opt` — a syntactic macro-guard tweak with potentially large synthesis-inference impact.\n\n**Core idea:** Implement lesson r4s0's named-but-untested path: guard the regfile reset-to-zero for-loop with `` `ifdef YOSYS `` + `` `ifndef RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS `` so that:\n- **Verilator / cocotb** → reset loop active (tests stay deterministic)\n- **Per-iteration formal** (ALTOPS mode per `formal/checks.cfg:45`) → reset loop active (`reg_ch*` BMC induction anchor preserved, so r3s0's failure mode cannot recur)\n- **Gowin FPGA yosys synth** (`fpga/scripts/synth.tcl`, no extra defines) → reset loop dropped, enabling distributed-SSRAM / SDPB inference for the 32×32 regfile\n\nExpected gain: ~1024 FFs reclaimed + associated reset-network LUTs freed, which on the near-full GW2AR fabric (9484/10000 LUT4) should lift Fmax via reduced congestion — mirroring the r1s0 multiplier-collapse pattern where physical-resource relief, not static-critical-path shortening, drove the gain.\n\nConfidence: medium (mechanical change; downside risk is Yosys's memory inference heuristics refusing distributed SSRAM for the two-read-port + write-first bypass pattern, in which case we get flops-without-reset — still a net savings on the reset network but not the full 1024 FF reclaim).","time":{"start":1777787450922,"end":1777787455571}}}
