{"type":"text","timestamp":1777788403145,"sessionID":"ses_21390e507ffeKuRsHBtKX02KGL","part":{"id":"prt_dec722b3b001P1C8ThCoTEmX0D","messageID":"msg_dec7225f5001CA5UNBW6baDP1c","sessionID":"ses_21390e507ffeKuRsHBtKX02KGL","type":"text","text":"Written `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r6s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary of the proposal:**\n\n- **Category:** micro_opt\n- **Target:** `rtl/mem_stage.sv` load-data extraction cone\n- **Change:** Replace the variable-shift-plus-slice pattern (`dmem_rdata >> (addr[1:0]*8)` → `shifted[7:0]`/`shifted[15:0]`) with explicit byte and halfword muxes indexed by `addr[1:0]`\n- **Why it should work:** r3s1's post-mortem explicitly identified `shift + sign/zero-extend` as the MEM pre-flop critical cone. Prior attempts around MEM added muxes (regressed) or touched the PC cone (regressed). This one strictly *shortens* the already-identified critical cone without touching any other structure.\n- **Why it should be safe:** Purely local to mem_stage; word-load path unchanged; misaligned-halfword arms are don't-care because `mem_misalign` already traps them; cocotb load tests + cosim ISS diff catch any semantic slip.\n- **Expected:** +3%, medium confidence — a cone-shortening move in the narrow window that hasn't been tried, on a fabric where area-freeing micro-ops have been the most reliable winners (r1s0, r4s2).","time":{"start":1777788398395,"end":1777788403143}}}
