{"type":"text","timestamp":1777790002067,"sessionID":"ses_213776ec0ffeEvzsRffxmSeYkT","part":{"id":"prt_dec8a9b640018dIcGPAS5lkZGq","messageID":"msg_dec8a959e0017v3S0VSNItS3NZ","sessionID":"ses_213776ec0ffeEvzsRffxmSeYkT","type":"text","text":"Wrote the hypothesis. Summary:\n\n**hyp-20260503-001-r7s0**: Flatten ex_stage redirect_target to a single 2:1 mux on `is_jalr`, since the `!is_jalr` arm of jump_target is `pc+imm` — identical to branch_target. Also pre-compute `is_jump && !jal_predicted` at ID into a ctrl bit. Both land on the post-r4s2 PC-redirect critical path that's now exposed by the ID-JAL fast-path's added PC mux. Bitwise-equivalent refactors — formal unaffected, IPC unchanged, target is Fmax via LUT-depth reduction on GW2AR. +3%, medium confidence.","time":{"start":1777789999972,"end":1777790002064}}}
