{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777791827994,"sessionID":"ses_2135add8affeu0S6g7IlssIi6u","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bdrk_0116DUGiZ3BmWWyXYWfzRPZ8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r8s0.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260503-001-r8s0\ntitle: \"Flatten ex_stage redirect_target to a single is_jalr 2:1 mux (no struct edits)\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The EX-stage redirect_target cone currently has two mux levels stacked:\n  first jump_target picks between {jalr_sum[31:1],1'b0} and (in.pc + in.imm)\n  on is_jalr, then redirect_target picks between jump_target and branch_target\n  on is_jump. But branch_target is literally `in.pc + in.imm`, identical to\n  jump_target's non-JALR arm. So the outer is_jump mux is structurally\n  redundant: every non-JALR taken-redirect (both JAL and taken-BRANCH)\n  resolves to in.pc + in.imm, and the only architecturally-distinct case is\n  JALR, which picks {jalr_sum[31:1],1'b0}.\n  redirect_target feeds core.sv's EX-vs-ID arbitration mux (2:1) then\n  if_stage's PC-select mux (2:1) then the PC D-input — i.e. this net is on\n  the fetch-redirect critical cone that has repeatedly dominated Fmax on\n  this near-full (9484 / 10000 LUT4) GW2AR fabric. Shaving one LUT-level\n  here is the micro-opt version of r4s2's \"resolve earlier / share the\n  existing redirect wire\" recipe, with zero new storage and no new predictor\n  arm.\nhypothesis: |\n  In ex_stage.sv, replace `assign redirect_target = in.ctrl.is_jump ?\n  jump_target : branch_target;` with a direct single-level mux:\n  `assign redirect_target = in.ctrl.is_jalr ? {jalr_sum[31:1], 1'b0} :\n  (in.pc + in.imm);`\n  Yosys should CSE the `in.pc + in.imm` adder with the existing\n  branch_target / jump_target adders (same inputs, same operator), so this\n  is purely a mux-level reduction on the is_jalr select, not a new adder.\n  The existing `jump_target` and `branch_target` locals stay in place and\n  keep feeding the EX/MEM register's branch_target field plus the pc_next\n  priority mux — we do NOT delete them, do NOT rename them, and do NOT\n  touch the id_ex_t / ex_mem_t struct layout (per r7s0's tarpit lesson:\n  struct-field renames destabilize the SBY reg_ch0 BMC). The EX `redirect`\n  assert is unchanged: `(branch_taken || (in.ctrl.is_jump &&\n  !in.jal_predicted)) && !misalign_fault`; redirect_target is just\n  architecturally-dead when redirect=0 so the simplified form is safe for\n  non-JALR-non-jump-non-branch cycles (the old form was equally dead in\n  those cycles — redirect_target was a don't-care).\n  Correctness: for every cycle redirect=1, the new redirect_target equals\n  the old one: JALR case → {jalr_sum[31:1],1'b0} (identical), JAL case →\n  in.pc + in.imm (old path: jump_target with is_jalr=0 → in.pc + in.imm;\n  outer mux with is_jump=1 → jump_target, identical), taken-BRANCH case →\n  in.pc + in.imm (old path: branch_target = in.pc + in.imm, identical).\n  JAL fast-path cycles where EX's redirect is masked by jal_predicted are\n  unaffected since redirect=0 makes redirect_target don't-care regardless.\n  Misalign trap cycles set redirect=0 so redirect_target is don't-care\n  there too.\n  Expected effect: one LUT-level shorter on the fetch-redirect cone →\n  small Fmax lift (1-3%) on GW2AR. IPC unchanged (this is a pure\n  combinational restructuring — no pipeline-timing changes, no new\n  predictor state, no new hazard). Formal impact should be nil since every\n  redirect=1 cycle produces bit-identical targets and no struct/port edits\n  occur.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Replace the `assign redirect_target = in.ctrl.is_jump ? jump_target : branch_target;` line with `assign redirect_target = in.ctrl.is_jalr ? {jalr_sum[31:1], 1'b0} : (in.pc + in.imm);`. Leave `jump_target`, `branch_target`, `jalr_sum`, and the `ex_mem_t` register writes (including reg_q.branch_target) untouched. Do not modify any struct in core_pkg.sv. Do not touch id_ex_t.jal_predicted or the EX `redirect` assert's boolean form. The `/* verilator lint_off UNUSEDSIGNAL */` guard around jalr_sum stays — the new redirect_target uses bits [31:1] so the lint-off can remain as-is or be narrowed; keep it as-is to minimize diff surface.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r8s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r8s0.yaml","time":{"start":1777791827981,"end":1777791827992}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_deca62cf2001b4gP4wRkHSZ9pI","sessionID":"ses_2135add8affeu0S6g7IlssIi6u","messageID":"msg_deca627d7001En3ZkDAZLrTzSC"}}
