{"type":"text","timestamp":1777791833583,"sessionID":"ses_2135add8affeu0S6g7IlssIi6u","part":{"id":"prt_deca68511001GAGvLy0EewQNmc","messageID":"msg_deca6805e001HUNPGnQF6C8jzy","sessionID":"ses_2135add8affeu0S6g7IlssIi6u","type":"text","text":"Wrote hypothesis `hyp-20260503-001-r8s0` at `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r8s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** Flatten `redirect_target` in `ex_stage.sv` to a single 2:1 mux on `is_jalr`. The outer `is_jump ? jump_target : branch_target` mux is structurally redundant because `branch_target` and `jump_target`'s non-JALR arm are both `in.pc + in.imm`. New form: `redirect_target = is_jalr ? {jalr_sum[31:1], 1'b0} : (in.pc + in.imm)`.\n\n**Why this avoids prior tarpits:**\n- No `id_ex_t` / `ex_mem_t` struct edits (avoids r7s0's rename-destabilizes-SBY trap)\n- No predictor state, no new ID-side fire arm, no widening of `redirect_target` past 2:1 (avoids r6s2 / r7s2)\n- No ALU operand mux widening — the parallel `in.pc + in.imm` adders stay parallel with ALU (avoids r2s0 / r7s1)\n- Bit-identical outputs on every `redirect=1` cycle, so formal should be unperturbed\n\n**Expected:** 1–3% Fmax lift from one shaved LUT-level on the fetch-redirect critical cone; IPC unchanged.","time":{"start":1777791829265,"end":1777791833581}}}
