{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777792925001,"sessionID":"ses_2134abfcaffe4KQES1L5K9Huyy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bdrk_0126dgvBs2FLCtRYFteA9y8c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r9s0.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260503-001-r9s0\ntitle: \"Unified barrel shifter: implement SLL as bit-reversed SRL/SRA to reclaim LUTs\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The ALU currently instantiates three independent shift expressions —\n  `a << shamt` (SLL), `a >> shamt` (SRL), and `$signed(a) >>> shamt` (SRA) —\n  each of which Yosys/Gowin synthesizes as a full 32-bit barrel shifter.\n  SRL and SRA already share the shifter structurally (fill-bit select), but\n  SLL is the opposite direction and lands as a second full barrel\n  (~90 LUT4s). The current FPGA is near-full at 9484/10000 LUT4s (94.8%);\n  recent lessons (r2s2, r3s2, r6s2) repeatedly pin regressions on routing\n  congestion and LUT-headroom pressure on GW2AR rather than raw logic\n  depth, so reclaiming area off a non-critical combinational cone is a\n  safe class of micro_opt on this fabric. The shift cone is NOT the ALU\n  Fmax critical path (the combinational divider dominates), so trading\n  one extra LUT level of bit-reverse muxes for one fewer full barrel is\n  strictly area-positive and Fmax-neutral.\nhypothesis: |\n  Fold SLL into the existing SRL/SRA shifter using the standard\n  bit-reverse trick: unconditionally reverse the input (bit[i] <-> bit[31-i])\n  on an SLL op, perform a right-shift with SRA-style fill-bit selection,\n  then conditionally reverse the output on SLL. A bit-reverse is free\n  wires at elaboration (just a permutation), so the implementation cost is\n  two 32-bit 2:1 muxes (`is_sll ? reverse(x) : x`) gating the input and\n  output of a single shared right-shifter. Net change:\n    - Remove: one full 32-bit barrel-shifter cone (~80–100 LUT4s)\n    - Add:    two 32-bit 2:1 muxes (~64 LUT4s)\n    - Depth: shift path grows by 1 LUT level (6 vs 5), still well under\n             the combinational divider / case-mux cone that sets ALU Fmax.\n  This is a strictly local edit to `rtl/alu.sv`. It does not touch:\n    - id_ex_t / ex_mem_t / mem_wb_t (per r7s0, r4s1, r8s0 lessons)\n    - the redirect_target cone (r8s0, r8s1)\n    - the MEM load-data cone (r6s0)\n    - the regfile reset/init pattern (r3s0, r5s0, r6s1)\n    - the JAL/JALR link path (r4s1, r5s1)\n  Bit-exactness is guaranteed by construction: `reverse(reverse(a) >> s)`\n  equals `a << s` for all 32-bit `a` and 5-bit `s` because the reverse\n  permutation is self-inverse and the right-shift's zero-fill maps to the\n  left-shift's zero-fill after the outer reverse. RV32M arithmetic is\n  untouched (no change to the multiplier or divider arms). The ALTOPS\n  branch is also untouched (shifts are not ALTOPS-substituted). Formal\n  risk is minimal: the ALU has no pipeline registers, no RVFI-visible\n  state, and the affected signal (`out` for op in {SLL, SRL, SRA}) must\n  remain bitwise identical to pass `test_alu.py` and the RVFI shift-op\n  checks.\n  Confidence is medium — area savings of ~30–50 LUT4s on a 94.8%-full\n  fabric plausibly unlocks better placement and routing slack (the\n  mechanism behind several prior Fmax wins that were NOT predicted by\n  logic-depth analysis alone), but the magnitude of the Fmax/routing\n  improvement is inherently noisy at this area-pressure level.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n  confidence: medium\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: \"Replace the three independent shift arms (SLL, SRL, SRA) with a single shared right-shifter. Add helper wires: `shift_in = is_sll ? {a[0],a[1],...,a[31]} : a;` (reversed for SLL). Compute `shift_fill = (op == ALU_SRA) ? a[31] : 1'b0` and perform `shifted = $signed({shift_fill, shift_in}) >>> shamt` (or equivalently a right-shift with explicit fill). Then `shift_out = is_sll ? reverse(shifted) : shifted;`. Wire `shift_out` into the ALU_SLL / ALU_SRL / ALU_SRA arms of the main `case (op)` mux. Keep MUL/DIV/REM arms and all other ops untouched. Preserve the ALTOPS `ifdef` branch verbatim.\"\n  - file: test/test_alu.py\n    description: \"Confirm existing shift vectors still pass; no new vectors required since bit-exact equivalence is a structural property. If the suite lacks edge cases at shamt=0 and shamt=31 for all three shift ops on patterns {0x00000000, 0xFFFFFFFF, 0x80000001, 0x5A5A5A5A}, add them as a regression guard for the bit-reverse symmetry.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r9s0.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r9s0.yaml","time":{"start":1777792924987,"end":1777792924998}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_decb6df39001C7rjYdTIOgoOdA","sessionID":"ses_2134abfcaffe4KQES1L5K9Huyy","messageID":"msg_decb6d6760016idN6vLl7GETBs"}}
