{"type":"text","timestamp":1777792929329,"sessionID":"ses_2134abfcaffe4KQES1L5K9Huyy","part":{"id":"prt_decb74281001DBy2IEwgsENLoE","messageID":"msg_decb73d91001C2NAt64ILQxnWF","sessionID":"ses_2134abfcaffe4KQES1L5K9Huyy","type":"text","text":"Wrote `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-001-r9s0.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** Unify the ALU's three shift arms into a single shared right-shifter by implementing SLL as `reverse(reverse(a) >> shamt)`. Bit-reverse is free wires; cost is two 32-bit 2:1 muxes, savings is one full barrel shifter (~30-50 LUT4s net). Strictly local to `rtl/alu.sv` — avoids every documented tarpit (id_ex_t, redirect cone, MEM load-data, regfile reset, JAL/JALR link). Targets area-driven routing improvement on the 94.8%-full GW2AR fabric rather than logic-depth Fmax; shifts are not the ALU critical path (the combinational divider is), so +1 LUT level on the shifter is Fmax-neutral. Medium confidence, +3% expected.","time":{"start":1777792926337,"end":1777792929326}}}
