 the unit becomes single-cycle with the XOR-of-add substitution mirrored from alu.sv so formal still closes.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/ex_stage.sv\", \"description\": \"Instantiate mul_div alongside alu. Detect MUL/DIV class opcodes (alu_op >= ALU_MUL). On first cycle: pulse `mul_div.start`, assert new output `stall_mul_div` until `done`. Final result mux between alu_result and mul_div.result drives EX/MEM.alu_result. Preserve forwarding \\u2014 mul_div.result feeds fwd_ex_mem once the op has landed in EX/MEM.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/hazard_unit.sv\", \"description\": \"Add input `mul_div_busy`. OR it into stall_if / stall_id (freeze IF and hold ID/EX register) and clear flush_id while busy (don't insert a load-use-style bubble). stall_ex_mem stays 0 (EX/MEM captures on `done`). hold_mem_wb asserts while busy so the prior retirement's MEM/WB forwarding payload stays alive.\"}, {\"file\": \"rtl/core.sv\", \"description\": \"Wire ex_stage's `stall_mul_div` into hazard_unit's new `mul_div_busy` input. No change to IO or RVFI ports.\"}, {\"file\": \"test/test_alu.py\", \"description\": \"Update the ALU cocotb harness: MUL/DIV vectors now test the new `mul_div` DUT separately (2-cycle MUL latency, 33-cycle DIV latency). Add a stall-handshake test that verifies `busy` stays high for the entire operation and `done` pulses exactly once. Keep coverage for all 8 M-ext ops with the existing 30+ vectors each.\"}, {\"file\": \"test/test_pipeline.py\", \"description\": \"Add a test that inserts a MUL followed by a dependent ADD and verifies IF/ID are frozen for the expected 2 cycles, then ADD retires with the correct rd_wdata. Add a DIV-by-zero + DIV by -1 of INT_MIN + generic signed DIV trio and verify rvfi_rd_wdata matches RV32M semantics field-by-field.\"}]}, \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\": 12, \"confidence\": \"medium\"}, \"changes\": [{\"file\": \"rtl/alu.sv\", \"description\": \"Remove MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU/DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU from the combinational ALU. On those opcodes