eline.py\", \"description\": \"Add a test that inserts a MUL followed by a dependent ADD and verifies IF/ID are frozen for the expected 2 cycles, then ADD retires with the correct rd_wdata. Add a DIV-by-zero + DIV by -1 of INT_MIN + generic signed DIV trio and verify rvfi_rd_wdata matches RV32M semantics field-by-field.\"}], \"outcome\": \"regression\", \"fitness\": 301.04, \"delta_pct\": 0.0, \"vs_baseline\": 0.0, \"fmax_mhz\": 135.21, \"ipc_coremark\": 2e-06, \"cycles\": 4491485, \"iterations\": 10, \"lut4\": 9880, \"ff\": 1858, \"seeds\": [121.29, 135.21, 136.07], \"formal_passed\": true, \"cosim_passed\": true, \"error\": null, \"implementation_notes\": \"\", \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-03T04:42:59.919457Z\", \"slot\": 1, \"round_id\": 1, \"lesson\": \"- 2026-05-03 hyp-20260503-002-r1s1 (regression, +0.00%): Once the shared 33x33 multiplier already sits off the EX forward-mux critical path, moving MUL/DIV into a multi-cycle handshake unit adds stall logic in hazard_unit and a new busy/done path without freeing Fmax, so CoreMark's matrix-kernel MUL density turns the extra stall cycles into a net IPC loss \\u2014 pipelining MUL/DIV only pays when the combinational multiplier is provably the critical path, otherwise measure first.\"}\n","exit":0,"description":"Check log.jsonl structure","truncated":false},"title":"Check log.jsonl structure","time":{"start":1777794527631,"end":1777794527633}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_deccfb006001mBKDdJ7AFD5tpv","sessionID":"ses_21332ad4dffeXdWVjP6a45RONf","messageID":"msg_deccfa7920018vGvc6GcE9zxP0"}}
