{"type":"text","timestamp":1777802998242,"sessionID":"ses_212b69be8ffeSqg2Tx8NnwQmcg","part":{"id":"prt_ded50dafe001m0wglkafHLuKUB","messageID":"msg_ded50d2070012apbP1Y0TPtgem","sessionID":"ses_212b69be8ffeSqg2Tx8NnwQmcg","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r15s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary of proposal**: Structural decomposition of the monolithic `alu.sv` (19-arm case mux) into three parallel combinational sub-modules — `alu_arith` (8 I-ext ops), `alu_shift` (3-op barrel), `alu_mext` (8 M-ext ops, preserving r1s0's shared 33×33 multiplier and ALTOPS branch intact) — with a 4:1 op-class output mux in the top-level `alu` wrapper.\n\n**Key differentiators from prior ALU attempts**:\n- Distinct from r1s1 (multi-cycle M-ext with stall handshake): zero new pipeline state, zero stall-cone impact, pure combinational 0-cycle latency preserved\n- Distinct from r14s0 (port-threaded sharing): uses actual module instantiation, which Gowin's nextpnr-himbaechel may consume as placement hints even if Yosys flattens the netlist\n- External `alu` port contract unchanged → ex_stage unchanged → zero formal-tarpit risk classes (no struct edits, no fetch-redirect cone, no RVFI shift, no shadow flops, no reset-loop touch)\n\n**Honest risk call**: expected gain is congestion-routing relief on the 94.8%-full GW2AR, not combinational depth reduction. If Yosys flatten erases hierarchy before nextpnr sees it, delta = 0%. Confidence set to low accordingly (+3% estimate).","time":{"start":1777802992382,"end":1777802998239}}}
