{"type":"text","timestamp":1777783718205,"sessionID":"ses_213d960adffeY7h4S9ndBjAhb5","part":{"id":"prt_dec2aada20018llLTTz1wrVsSp","messageID":"msg_dec2aa3c9001SdHzShDQQs37Fj","sessionID":"ses_213d960adffeY7h4S9ndBjAhb5","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written at `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r2s1.yaml`.\n\nSummary:\n- **Category:** structural\n- **Title:** Decoupled IF/ID via 1-entry prefetch skid buffer to absorb iStall bubbles\n- **Core idea:** Split IF into `fetch_pc`/`commit_pc` with a 1-entry {valid,pc,instr} buffer. Fill during ID-stalled cycles (load-use/dStall) when imem is ready; drain during iStall cycles instead of forcing NOP. Directly recovers retirements lost to the 22% iStall methodology.\n- **Key contrast with failed hyp-003:** buffer sits on the `imem_data → ID` datapath, not the PC flop's combinational cone. PC's next-state mux and the EX→IF redirect path are untouched.\n- **Expected impact:** +4%, medium confidence. Fmax neutral (only a registered 1-entry buffer + 2:1 output mux added, away from known critical paths).\n- **Changes scoped to:** `rtl/if_stage.sv` (restructure), `rtl/hazard_unit.sv` (gate flush_if by buffer.valid), `rtl/core.sv` (1 new signal wiring), `test/test_pipeline.py` (4 new buffer-behavior tests including RVFI-order monotonicity on redirect-invalidates-buffer case).\n- **Orthogonal to other r2 slots:** r2s0 (shared subtractor) targets EX ALU logic; r2s2 (BTB) targets branch prediction; r2s1 targets fetch-bandwidth decoupling — no overlap.","time":{"start":1777783713186,"end":1777783718203}}}
