{"type":"text","timestamp":1777786209333,"sessionID":"ses_213b401fbffeeZdL7EzK147fQT","part":{"id":"prt_dec50afc0003onGuapDGubWASK","messageID":"msg_dec50a84b001mjgI3piY11h9Xr","sessionID":"ses_213b401fbffeeZdL7EzK147fQT","type":"text","text":"Written hypothesis `hyp-20260503-002-r4s1` at `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r4s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: Structural — hoist JAL/JALR link-register value (PC+4) out of EX stage by reusing the IF stage's already-existing `pc + 32'd4` adder. Adds a `link_val` field to if_id_t / id_ex_t; replaces EX's `in.ctrl.is_jump ? (in.pc + 32'd4) : alu_result` with `in.ctrl.is_jump ? in.link_val : alu_result`, deleting one redundant 32-bit carry-chain adder from the EX cone into EX/MEM's alu_result register.\n\n**Rationale vs. lessons**:\n- Prior structural attempts (r1s1, r2s1, r3s1) all *added* logic depth in critical cones and regressed. This hypothesis *strictly removes* logic from EX — no new mux fan-in, no new stall logic, no IPC change.\n- Predictor/storage attempts (r2s2 BTB, r3s2 RAS) lost to LUT pressure at 9905/10000 utilization; this change *frees* ~30 LUTs (one 32-bit adder), pushing the opposite direction on the same congestion axis.\n- IPC identical (JAL/JALR still link PC+4). RVFI rd_wdata bit-equivalent. Formal invariants untouched.\n\nExpected fitness delta: +2%, medium confidence. Upside capped (small pc+4 adder unlikely to be the sole critical cone vs. shared multiplier), downside floor is roughly neutral (LUT reclaim can't regress).","time":{"start":1777786204096,"end":1777786209332}}}
