{"type":"text","timestamp":1777787357273,"sessionID":"ses_213a0ffceffe6YVWFPqTuEDSSK","part":{"id":"prt_dec623f15001xqEYEX7Q0uB0a8","messageID":"msg_dec6238aa001CA540j69W4P2fU","sessionID":"ses_213a0ffceffe6YVWFPqTuEDSSK","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r5s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** Structural refactor that folds JAL/JALR's pc+4 link value into the ALU's idle-for-jumps adder by steering pre-ALU operand muxes to `(pc, 4)` when `is_jump`. This deletes the post-ALU 2:1 link mux and its dedicated +4 adder — both currently sit on the fwd_ex_mem forwarding cone. No new FFs, no pipeline-register plumbing (distinguishing from r4s1's regression), and the pre-ALU mux depth stays at 1 LUT4 per bit. Expected: one LUT level off EX's critical forwarding path plus ~60 LUTs reclaimed.","time":{"start":1777787354901,"end":1777787357271}}}
