{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777790073377,"sessionID":"ses_213776dfdffecrYqQbMmcvyfjT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bdrk_01TeThuvTPMPT7wPpyfFvnd6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r7s1.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260503-002-r7s1\ntitle: \"Unified target-address adder: share one pc/rs1 + imm cell for BRANCH/JAL/JALR targets\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  ex_stage.sv currently instantiates three independent 32-bit adders whose\n  operand sets overlap heavily with the ALU's own internal ADD cone:\n    1) the ALU's adder (rs1+imm for JALR/LOAD/STORE/OP-IMM-ADDI/R-ADD,\n       pc+imm for AUIPC);\n    2) `branch_target = in.pc + in.imm` (used by the BRANCH redirect arm);\n    3) `jalr_sum     = rs1   + in.imm` (used by JALR's {sum[31:1],0} target).\n  Yosys cannot CSE (2) or (3) into the ALU's adder because the ALU's\n  operand-select muxes (`alu_a = is_auipc ? pc : rs1; alu_b = alu_src ?\n  imm : rs2`) don't cover BRANCH (alu_src=0 feeds rs2) or JAL (alu_src=0,\n  is_auipc=0) so the structural operand cones differ, and the two spare\n  adders get synthesised as distinct Gowin ALU/carry slices.\n  r1s0's +9.47% win on the shared 33-bit multiplier shows that collapsing\n  parallel duplicate arithmetic cells into one shared cell is a Fmax/LUT\n  winner on this near-full (9484/10000 LUT4) GW2AR fabric — the structural\n  analogue on the *additive* side has not been tried, and the three\n  in-EX adders plus the ALU's ADD are exactly that pattern.\nhypothesis: |\n  Unify the target-address arithmetic into a single explicit pre-case-mux\n  ALU-adder wire and feed branch_target, JAL target, and JALR target\n  from it, retiring the two duplicate EX-local adders. Steps:\n    * Widen ex_stage's ALU operand mux: alu_a = (is_auipc | is_branch |\n      is_jump_non_jalr) ? pc : rs1 ; alu_b = (alu_src | is_branch |\n      is_jump_non_jalr) ? imm : rs2. JALR keeps the existing alu_src=1\n      route (rs1+imm). BRANCH / JAL now feed (pc,imm) into the ALU.\n    * Inside alu.sv expose `alu_add_out = alu_a + alu_b` as a dedicated\n      output wire (separate from the case-mux'd `out`), so the redirect\n      path does NOT pay the ALU case-mux depth for branch/jump targets.\n    * ex_stage: drop the local `branch_target = pc+imm` and\n      `jalr_sum = rs1+imm` adders; compute\n        branch_target = alu_add_out;\n        jump_target   = in.ctrl.is_jalr ? {alu_add_out[31:1], 1'b0}\n                                        : alu_add_out;\n    * Behavioural invariants preserved:\n        - alu_result's observable value (post-case-mux) is unchanged for\n          opcodes that use it (R-type/OP-IMM/LOAD/STORE/AUIPC/LUI/JALR\n          still see rs1/pc operand and correct case output). For BRANCH\n          and JAL the post-case-mux alu_result is now pc+imm instead of\n          the previous rs1+rs2 (BRANCH) / rs1+rs2 (JAL), but those values\n          are never consumed: BRANCH has reg_write=0, and JAL has\n          `reg_q.alu_result <= (pc+4)` overriding it at the flop.\n        - The parallel branch comparator (rs1 vs rs2) is untouched — r2s0\n          regressed precisely from serialising compare through the ALU,\n          which this hypothesis does NOT do.\n        - redirect_target mux stays 2:1 (jump_target vs branch_target),\n          if_stage PC D-input stays 2:1 — no new PC-mux fanin (the r2s2\n          / r3s2 / r6s2 failure mode is avoided).\n        - RVFI fields, decoder, regfile and formal state are unchanged;\n          no macro guards, no initial blocks, no reset-loop deletions\n          (the r3s0 / r4s0 / r5s0 / r6s1 formal tarpits are avoided).\n  Expected wins: ~40–80 LUT4 reclaimed (two 32-bit ripple adders with\n  their operand wiring), which on the 9484/10000 fabric eases GW2AR\n  placement/routing and should recover 1–3% Fmax. No IPC change\n  (retirement cycle counts are identical; this is purely an area/Fmax\n  restructure).\n  Risk: if Yosys already silently shared these adders via some internal\n  commutative-add CSE pass, the diff is a no-op. Mitigation: keep the\n  change minimal and structurally additive; no formal-visible state\n  changes so the floor is \"neutral\", not \"regression\".\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n  confidence: low\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n    description: \"Add a dedicated `output logic [31:0] alu_add_out` port driven by `alu_a + alu_b` before the case-mux, so downstream consumers can tap the ADD cone without paying the 19-way case-mux depth.\"\n  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n    description: \"Widen the alu_a/alu_b operand muxes so BRANCH and JAL route (pc, imm) to the ALU (JALR stays rs1+imm via existing alu_src=1). Connect the new alu.alu_add_out port; use it to drive branch_target (= alu_add_out) and jump_target (= is_jalr ? {alu_add_out[31:1],1'b0} : alu_add_out). Delete the local `branch_target = in.pc + in.imm` and `jalr_sum = rs1 + in.imm` wires and their adders. Keep the branch comparator, misalign-fault check, `reg_q.alu_result <= is_jump ? pc+4 : alu_result` override, and pc_next formula exactly as-is.\"\n  - file: test/test_pipeline.py\n    description: \"Add a targeted cocotb check confirming BRANCH-taken, JAL, and JALR all produce the same architectural pc_wdata as before this change (spot-check: BEQ taken with imm=+8, JAL imm=-12, JALR rs1=0x100 imm=+4), guarding against a subtle operand-routing regression that RVFI-unique/formal-ill alone might not surface.\"\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r7s1.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r7s1.yaml","time":{"start":1777790073372,"end":1777790073376}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_dec8b500d001XsFQg9X51ibLGi","sessionID":"ses_213776dfdffecrYqQbMmcvyfjT","messageID":"msg_dec8b49d2001XsL4gRUXZveYp5"}}
