{"type":"text","timestamp":1777790080436,"sessionID":"ses_213776dfdffecrYqQbMmcvyfjT","part":{"id":"prt_dec8bc3d9001BIxAG8xNgTCIGk","messageID":"msg_dec8bba55001U57LpT7qvmTFiQ","sessionID":"ses_213776dfdffecrYqQbMmcvyfjT","type":"text","text":"Wrote `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r7s1.yaml`.\n\n**Summary**: Structural hypothesis unifying three parallel 32-bit adders in ex_stage (ALU's internal ADD cone, `branch_target = pc+imm`, `jalr_sum = rs1+imm`) into one shared adder by widening the ALU's operand muxes to route (pc, imm) for BRANCH/JAL (JALR keeps rs1+imm via the existing alu_src=1 route) and exposing `alu_add_out` as a dedicated pre-case-mux wire for the redirect path.\n\n**Key lesson hooks**:\n- Mirrors r1s0's winning pattern (shared 33-bit multiplier, +9.47%) on the additive side.\n- Avoids r2s0's failure mode (does NOT route the branch comparator through the ALU — compare stays parallel).\n- Avoids r2s2/r3s2/r6s2 predictor-style PC-mux fanin growth (redirect_target mux stays 2:1).\n- Avoids r3s0/r4s0/r5s0/r6s1 formal tarpits (no regfile/reset/macro changes).\n- Avoids r5s1's link-value-into-ALU tarpit (the `is_jump ? pc+4 : alu_result` flop override is untouched).\n- Confidence set to `low` because if Yosys already silently CSEs these adders the diff is a no-op, but the structural floor should be neutral rather than regression.","time":{"start":1777790075865,"end":1777790080436}}}
