{"type":"text","timestamp":1777791939433,"sessionID":"ses_2135addceffe4De8hDdLDQJTTs","part":{"id":"prt_deca82746001fIYaIRnm6oHoY0","messageID":"msg_deca8221a0010Q7wmDUNrCyy8M","sessionID":"ses_2135addceffe4De8hDdLDQJTTs","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r8s1.yaml`.\n\nSummary: A structural reorganization of ex_stage's `redirect` cone from AND-of-OR (`(BT || J) && !misalign`) to OR-of-AND (`(BT && aligned_b) || (J && !JP && aligned_j)`). Bit-equivalent, entirely local to `ex_stage.sv`, no id_ex_t edit, no PC-mux widening, no cross-flop mux moves — satisfying the constraints that killed the 7 prior slot-1 structural attempts. The goal is to shave ~1 LUT level off the EX→IF redirect path by letting each arm's compare and alignment-check run in parallel (the `[1:0]==0` check resolves in the low carry-chain bits while the compare resolves at the head) instead of serially. Low confidence (+3%) because Yosys may already CSE this, but the risk profile is as benign as any structural change on this core gets.","time":{"start":1777791936326,"end":1777791939432}}}
