{"type":"text","timestamp":1777801379412,"sessionID":"ses_212cbccc7ffeh3dFaPYyREhAzM","part":{"id":"prt_ded37b9240018OWovJgzQXH05a","messageID":"msg_ded37a30c001DYHXWjrh05euMb","sessionID":"ses_212cbccc7ffeh3dFaPYyREhAzM","type":"text","text":"No prior attempt has targeted the `& if_id_w.valid` conjunct removal specifically. All failure modes point at structural changes to the winning cone; this is the only remaining angle that is (a) formal-safe by pure combinational tautology (NOT reachable-state-dependent like r13s2), (b) adds zero new logic, (c) doesn't rename/append id_ex_t fields, (d) doesn't widen the arbiter, (e) doesn't add fire terms, (f) doesn't delete alignment gates that BMC explores.","time":{"start":1777801345316,"end":1777801379410}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777801379426,"sessionID":"ses_212cbccc7ffeh3dFaPYyREhAzM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bdrk_01X8waYcG38KgPQRU2uGFtur","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-003-r14s2.yaml","content":"id: hyp-20260503-003-r14s2\ntitle: \"Slim JAL fast-path fire gate: drop structurally redundant `& if_id_w.valid` conjunct\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  After 13 predictor-slot iterations, r4s2's zero-storage JAL fast-path\n  (+17.73%) remains the sole predictor win on this core. Every extension\n  regressed: second ID-side fire term (r6s2 -23%, r7s2 -50%, r10s2 -20%,\n  r11s2 -26%, r12s2 -23%), widened redirect_target arbiter past 2:1\n  (r7s2, r10s2), new IF-side predecode adder (r8s2 -13%), equivalent\n  rewrite on the winning cone (r9s2 -19%), dead-field struct shrink\n  (r11s0 -23%), and delete-tautology gates that BMC explores (r13s2\n  broken). The predictor search space as traditionally conceived is\n  empirically exhausted on this fabric.\n\n  The ONE angle that has NOT been tried, and that avoids every named\n  failure mode in the lessons, is a minimal cone-shave INSIDE the r4s2\n  winning gate that is a pure combinational tautology (not reachable-\n  state-dependent). Specifically, in core.sv line ~134:\n\n      id_is_jal = (if_id_w.instr[6:0] == 7'b1101111) & if_id_w.valid;\n\n  The `& if_id_w.valid` conjunct is structurally redundant: if_stage\n  drives `out.instr = flush ? 32'h0000_0013 : imem_data` and\n  `out.valid = !flush`, so whenever valid=0 the instruction is forced\n  to ADDI x0,x0,0 whose opcode[6:0]=0010011 already fails the JAL\n  opcode compare (1101111). The conjunct is a combinational identity\n  tautology on the pair (instr[6:0], flush) — NOT a reachable-state\n  invariant like r13s2's pc-alignment (which BMC explored and falsified\n  from arbitrary initial states). No SBY BMC step can construct a case\n  where `instr[6:0]==1101111` holds while `valid=0`: the flush-NOP is\n  hardwired by the always_comb, so the implication is unconditional at\n  every simulated cycle.\nhypothesis: |\n  Remove the `& if_id_w.valid` conjunct from `id_is_jal` in core.sv,\n  leaving the fire gate as:\n\n      id_is_jal      = (if_id_w.instr[6:0] == 7'b1101111);\n      id_is_jal_fire = id_is_jal & !stall_id & id_jal_aligned;\n\n  This is a ONE-LINE edit: strip a single 2-input AND from the ID\n  redirect cone. Downstream logic is byte-identical:\n    - id_jal_aligned (the formal-load-bearing r13s2 gate) is preserved.\n    - The 2:1 `redirect_target` arbiter stays 2:1.\n    - No new ID-side fire term, no misprediction arm, no opcode beyond JAL.\n    - No storage / no tags / no new flops.\n    - No id_ex_t struct edit (r7s0 tarpit), no pipeline-register field\n      offset change (r11s0), no EX mask change, no alignment-gate\n      deletion (r13s2), no new adder (r8s2), no opcode-match\n      restructuring (r9s2 winning-cone rewrite tarpit).\n\n  Why this may help: on GW2AR the ID-side redirect fire cone is\n    imem_data[6:0]==1101111   (7-input equality, ~2 LUT4s)\n      AND flush-inverted valid (1 LUT4 — this is what we remove)\n      AND !stall_id            (1 LUT4)\n      AND id_jal_aligned       (1 LUT4 after the target add)\n    -> fans out to if_stage.redirect and hazard_unit-exempt combined\n       redirect wire.\n\n  Removing one level of AND-tree depth from a cone that the orchestrator\n  has independently identified as critical (r4s2's win was Fmax-bound\n  on exactly this net) is the textbook shallow-win pattern. Post-synth,\n  if Yosys's logic minimizer already sees the redundancy, the change is\n  a no-op (0% fitness delta, safe). If Yosys does NOT see the\n  redundancy (possible because `valid` is driven combinationally across\n  an instance boundary, so cross-module logic minimization may not\n  converge), we save ~1 LUT level on a cone that is measurably critical.\n\n  Why this is NOT r13s2: r13s2 deleted `id_jal_aligned` on the claim\n  that pc[1:0]==00 is invariant under correct execution. BMC explored\n  arbitrary post-reset pc states where that invariant is violated, and\n  the EX misalign-trap backstop fires one cycle too late. This\n  hypothesis deletes a gate whose tautology is a PURE COMBINATIONAL\n  identity on the same-cycle signals (instr[6:0], flush) driven by an\n  always_comb in if_stage — no reachable-state reasoning, no\n  multi-cycle invariant, no trap backstop required. BMC sees the same\n  function before and after.\n\n  Why this is NOT r9s2: r9s2 replaced `id_jal_target[1:0]==00` with\n  `!if_id_w.instr[21]` — a different expression on different signals\n  whose equivalence depends on multi-bit carry analysis of the\n  adder's low bits (plus the pc-alignment invariant). This\n  hypothesis just drops a conjunct whose equivalence is a 1-line\n  truth-table identity. The Yosys placement optimum for r4s2 may\n  still be disturbed (risk acknowledged — hence low confidence),\n  but unlike r9s2 the removed logic is a dangling input to the AND,\n  not a substituted sub-expression, so any CSE or cone-sharing Yosys\n  already found remains intact.\n\n  Risk: if Yosys already minimized this conjunct away (likely, given\n  the flush/valid relationship is visible within one module), the\n  change is a structural no-op and fitness delta is 0%. Placement\n  churn from any net name change is the only plausible regression\n  vector, and removing (rather than adding or substituting) is the\n  least churn-inducing of the three.\nexpected_impact:\n  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n  confidence: low\nchanges:\n  - file: rtl/core.sv\n    description: |\n      In the ID-stage JAL fast-path block (~line 134), change\n      `assign id_is_jal = (if_id_w.instr[6:0] == 7'b1101111) & if_id_w.valid;`\n      to `assign id_is_jal = (if_id_w.instr[6:0] == 7'b1101111);`.\n      All other lines unchanged. The fire gate `id_is_jal_fire = id_is_jal\n      & !stall_id & id_jal_aligned;` keeps its existing three conjuncts\n      — `stall_id` still blocks firing when dmem_stall / load-use\n      hazard / redirect consequences prevent the JAL from being\n      captured into id_ex, and `id_jal_aligned` remains the\n      formal-load-bearing alignment gate per r13s2. The `valid`\n      information is preserved downstream through if_stage's\n      combinational assertion that `out.instr = NOP` whenever `!valid`\n      — the NOP's opcode 0010011 never matches JAL's 1101111.\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-003-r14s2.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-003-r14s2.yaml","time":{"start":1777801379402,"end":1777801379424}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[{"type":"reasoning.text","text":" Since all other approaches have failed, I'm going to try removing just that one `& if_id_w.valid` condition and see if that's the issue — it's a long shot, but I'll document the hypothesis in YAML format.","format":"anthropic-claude-v1","index":0,"signature":""}]}},"id":"prt_ded37bf80001eao2Qt9F4ZlFf3","sessionID":"ses_212cbccc7ffeh3dFaPYyREhAzM","messageID":"msg_ded37a30c001DYHXWjrh05euMb"}}
