{"type":"text","timestamp":1777801387946,"sessionID":"ses_212cbccc7ffeh3dFaPYyREhAzM","part":{"id":"prt_ded384a520013zbiFHGd283ESD","messageID":"msg_ded383ea3001odjwHogLSha3oo","sessionID":"ses_212cbccc7ffeh3dFaPYyREhAzM","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-003-r14s2.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:**\n\nGiven the exhaustively-documented failure of 13 predictor-slot iterations — every extension, relocation, or equivalent rewrite of the r4s2 winning cone has regressed — I proposed the single remaining untried angle: a one-line removal of the structurally-redundant `& if_id_w.valid` conjunct from `id_is_jal`.\n\nKey properties that distinguish this from every named failure mode:\n- Pure combinational tautology on `(instr[6:0], flush)` — NOT a reachable-state invariant (unlike r13s2's pc-alignment which BMC falsified).\n- No id_ex_t edit (r7s0), no struct-offset change (r11s0), no new fire term (r6s2/r7s2/r10s2/r11s2/r12s2), no widened arbiter (r7s2/r10s2), no new adder (r8s2), no substituted sub-expression (r9s2), no alignment-gate deletion (r13s2).\n- The flush-NOP opcode (0010011) can never match JAL's opcode (1101111), making the `& valid` gate redundant by construction within the same always_comb.\n\nLow confidence (+2%) explicitly acknowledges that Yosys may already minimize the conjunct away (structural no-op, 0% delta) and that placement churn is the only plausible regression vector — minimized by removing rather than substituting.","time":{"start":1777801382482,"end":1777801387944}}}
