{"type":"text","timestamp":1777783590934,"sessionID":"ses_213d96018ffenZ3KaIfg9iR7Bw","part":{"id":"prt_dec28bf77001r1TwbIIY2MEQVE","messageID":"msg_dec28b633001TihJ6PwQgSmGdR","sessionID":"ses_213d96018ffenZ3KaIfg9iR7Bw","type":"text","text":"Written. The hypothesis proposes a 16-entry direct-mapped tagged BTB with the load-bearing discipline that fixes the prior predictor's Fmax cliff:\n\n**Key insight vs hyp-003-r1s2's failure:**\n- Prior attempt path: `imem_BRAM → predecode → adder → PC_reg` (long)\n- This attempt path: `PC_reg → BTB mux tree → tag cmp → FF_D` (ends at flop, not at PC_reg)\n- PC_reg's only new fan-in is `btb_pred_q` Q output (clean register output, one mux layer)\n\n**Penalty model:** 1 bubble on correct predict (down from 2), 2 bubbles on mispredict (same as today), 0 on BTB miss (default PC+4). No BTB hit means no prediction fires, so warmup and cold entries degrade gracefully.\n\n**Risk I flagged explicitly:** LUT budget is tight (9905/10000) — 16-entry BTB is ~928 FFs + ~100 LUTs; fall-back to 8-entry if synth rejects.","time":{"start":1777783586679,"end":1777783590932}}}
