{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777791999830,"sessionID":"ses_2135add1dffeUKxS3GwWxQAvhl","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_bdrk_0168FpRgvH2sfaAsU8X1DAzk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r8s1.yaml"},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/opus-4_7-rep3/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r8s1.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260503-002-r8s1\n2: title: \"Flatten EX redirect cone: distribute misalign into per-arm align-check\"\n3: category: structural\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The EX-stage `redirect` net feeds IF's PC-select mux and is on the\n6:   fetch-redirect critical path — any LUT-level we can remove there\n7:   translates directly into Fmax on GW2AR's near-full fabric. Today\n8:   the cone is an AND-of-OR structure: redirect = (BT || (J &&\n9:   !JP)) && !misalign_fault, where misalign_fault = (is_branch &&\n10:   BT && misalign_branch_target) || (is_jump && misalign_jump_target).\n11:   The branch_taken signal appears in BOTH operands of the outer AND\n12:   (directly in the first OR, and transitively via misalign_branch\n13:   in the second OR), forcing Yosys to realize the compare-compute\n14:   and align-check as a serial chain feeding the `redirect` wire\n15:   rather than two parallel-then-combined cones. This lengthens the\n16:   EX→IF redirect path by ~1 LUT level on this fabric.\n17: \n18:   Seven prior slot-1 structural attempts have all regressed or\n19:   broken formal — the survivors were those that stayed local (no\n20:   id_ex_t edit, no PC-mux widening, no cross-flop mux moves, no\n21:   new storage). This hypothesis is chosen to satisfy ALL of those\n22:   constraints simultaneously.\n23: hypothesis: |\n24:   Reorganize ex_stage.sv's `redirect` expression from AND-of-OR\n25:   (current form) to OR-of-AND (distributed form), folding the\n26:   misalign detection into each branch/jump arm independently:\n27: \n28:     branch_target_aligned = (branch_target[1:0] == 2'b00);\n29:     jump_target_aligned   = (jump_target[1:0]   == 2'b00);\n30:     redirect = (branch_taken && branch_target_aligned)\n31:             || (is_jump && !jal_predicted && jump_target_aligned);\n32: \n33:   The trap-side `ctrl_with_trap` and `pc_next` muxes stay unchanged\n34:   (same misalign_fault definition drives them, so RVFI trap\n35:   semantics are bit-identical). Only the `redirect` wire's cone is\n36:   reshaped. Equivalence: the current AND-of-OR form requires BOTH\n37:   (taken or jumping) AND (no misalign on whichever arm fires); the\n38:   distributed form checks (taken-and-aligned) OR (jumping-and-aligned),\n39:   which is the same boolean function because a taken branch and a\n40:   jump are mutually exclusive in any single instruction (is_branch\n41:   and is_jump are disjoint decoder outputs).\n42: \n43:   Why this should win on GW2AR: the `redirect` wire drives if_stage's\n44:   PC-register D-input mux (via the core.sv arbitration with\n45:   id_is_jal_fire). In the current form, `redirect`'s cone is\n46:   (compare-result → AND with align-check-of-a-pc+imm-adder), serial,\n47:   through two LUT4 levels. In the distributed form, each arm is\n48:   (compare AND align-check) computed independently, then OR'd —\n49:   Yosys can pack each arm into a single LUT4 (3-input AND) and the\n50:   final OR into a second LUT4, but critically the align-check runs\n51:   concurrently with the compare inside each arm rather than after,\n52:   because branch_target_aligned = (pc+imm)[1:0]==0 depends only on\n53:   the low 2 bits of the adder which resolve in LUT0 of the carry\n54:   chain while the compare resolves at the carry chain's head.\n55: \n56:   This is the mirror-image of r2s0's lesson (\"merging parallel cones\n57:   into one deeper serial cone trades area for Fmax in the wrong\n58:   direction\") applied in reverse: unmerging a serial cone into\n59:   parallel arms trades nothing for Fmax in the RIGHT direction. It's\n60:   also local to ex_stage.sv — no id_ex_t edit (r7s0, r5s2, r6s0\n61:   tarpit), no PC-select widening (r6s2), no cross-flop mux move\n62:   (r3s1, r4s1).\n63: \n64:   Expected gain: ~1 LUT level off the EX→IF redirect path on the\n65:   near-full GW2AR fabric, contributing +2–4% Fmax. IPC unchanged\n66:   (bit-equivalent redirect semantics). No new storage, no struct\n67:   edits, no formal contract touch.\n68: expected_impact:\n69:   fitness_delta_pct: 3\n70:   confidence: low\n71: changes:\n72:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n73:     description: \"Reorganize redirect assignment from AND-of-OR to OR-of-AND. Compute branch_target_aligned and jump_target_aligned as explicit signals; rewrite assign redirect = (branch_taken && branch_target_aligned) || (in.ctrl.is_jump && !in.jal_predicted && jump_target_aligned). Leave misalign_fault / ctrl_with_trap / reg_q.pc_next untouched (they still gate trap + linear-next-pc bit-identically). Redirect_target mux stays 2:1 (is_jump ? jump_target : branch_target) unchanged.\"\n74:   - file: test/test_pipeline.py\n75:     description: \"Add a cocotb assertion (if not already present) that a taken BRANCH with misaligned target produces rvfi_trap=1 on the retiring instruction and does NOT cause a PC redirect (next retirement's pc_rdata = trapping_pc + 4). Similarly for misaligned JAL and JALR. Ensures the distributed form preserves the trap-suppresses-redirect invariant.\"\n\n(End of file - total 75 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260503-002-r8s1\ntitle: \"Flatten EX redirect cone: distribute misalign into per-arm align-check\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The EX-stage `redirect` net feeds IF's PC-select mux and is on the\n  fetch-redirect critical path — any LUT-level we can remove there\n  translates directly into Fmax on GW2AR's near-full fabric. Today\n  the cone is an AND-of-OR structure: redirect = (BT || (J &&\n  !JP)) && !misalign_fault, where misalign_fault = (is_branch &&\n  BT && misalign_branch_target) || (is_jump && misalign_jump_target).\n  The branch_taken signal appears in BOTH operands of the outer AND\n  (directly in the first OR, and transitively via misalign_branch\n  in the second OR), forcing Yosys to realize the compare-compute\n  and align-check as a serial chain feeding the `redirect` wire\n  rather than two parallel-then-combined cones. This lengthens the\n  EX→IF redirect path by ~1 LUT level on this fabric.\n\n  Seven prior slot-1 structural attempts have all regressed or\n  broken formal — the survivors were those that stayed local (no\n  id_ex_t edit, no PC-mux widening, no cross-flop mux moves, no","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-002-r8s1.yaml","time":{"start":1777791999825,"end":1777791999829}},"metadata":{"openrouter":{"reasoning_details":[]}},"id":"prt_deca91adc001jgbq0Kt95eI14u","sessionID":"ses_2135add1dffeUKxS3GwWxQAvhl","messageID":"msg_deca91269001g2cuoGP0CIyKTN"}}
