{"type":"text","timestamp":1777792060842,"sessionID":"ses_2135add1dffeUKxS3GwWxQAvhl","part":{"id":"prt_deca9f9d2001X8geDFPqC7eooM","messageID":"msg_deca9f3ad001RCeDo7BmqrgpqL","sessionID":"ses_2135add1dffeUKxS3GwWxQAvhl","type":"text","text":"Hypothesis written to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260503-003-r8s2.yaml`.\n\n**Summary:** Predictor-category move that **preserves the r4s2 JAL fast-path's winning structural recipe** but relocates its 32-bit adder off the ID→PC-D-in combinational cone by pre-registering the JAL target at IF.\n\nConstraints it respects (all derived from prior failed predictor lessons):\n- No new PC-select mux input (r1s2/r3s2/r7s2 tarpit)\n- No widened EX `redirect_target` mux (r6s2 tarpit — no misprediction arm)\n- No `id_ex_t` struct rename or new field (r7s0 tarpit)\n- No tag/CAM/BTB storage (r2s2 area tarpit)\n- Targets JAL only — unconditional, zero-mispredict recipe from r4s2\n\nExpected: +3% fitness, **low** confidence — gain is contingent on whether the ID→PC-D cone was an active Fmax constraint after r4s2 (if not, it's ~0%). The main risk is that the new IF-side parallel adder could tip IF critical, though it runs in parallel with the existing `imm_gen` J-type arm at the same pipeline boundary.","time":{"start":1777792055762,"end":1777792060841}}}
